WEBVTT

00:36.161 --> 00:38.955
WE ARE ALL TRYING HERE

00:40.040 --> 00:43.126
HYOWON MANSION

00:53.136 --> 00:54.429
Where do you live?

00:55.221 --> 00:56.765
I'll scatter 500-won coins for you!

00:57.390 --> 00:58.433
Where do you live?

01:04.355 --> 01:07.275
A while back,
one of my students wrote a story.

01:07.358 --> 01:11.529
A girl had finally gotten a chance
to go on a date with her long-time crush,

01:11.613 --> 01:14.157
but she overslept and showed up late.

01:14.240 --> 01:15.241
I lost it reading that.

01:15.325 --> 01:18.620
I said to my student, "Hey, if it were me,
I'd have gotten up at dawn to get ready."

01:18.703 --> 01:20.080
"I wouldn't have been able to sleep."

01:20.163 --> 01:23.666
"How could she oversleep on the day
she was supposed to meet her crush?"

01:24.250 --> 01:26.252
And you know what they said?

01:26.961 --> 01:29.964
"When I feel loved,

01:30.048 --> 01:31.674
I feel at ease and sleep deeply,

01:32.509 --> 01:33.843
like I've never slept before."

01:36.888 --> 01:38.139
I slept like a baby last night.

02:10.713 --> 02:13.216
DONG-MAN: I SLEPT LIKE A BABY LAST NIGHT

02:16.386 --> 02:17.637
DONG-MAN

02:24.185 --> 02:25.145
What are you talking about?

02:25.228 --> 02:27.480
As I said, I slept well last night.

02:28.231 --> 02:29.607
Good for you for sleeping well.

02:30.275 --> 02:31.734
I didn't sleep a wink.

02:32.318 --> 02:33.903
Why?

02:34.487 --> 02:36.614
I sent my screenplay to Eun-a,

02:37.740 --> 02:39.159
but I haven't heard back yet.

02:40.743 --> 02:41.870
I'm nervous.

02:41.953 --> 02:45.331
Is it time for your features to vanish?

02:46.666 --> 02:47.542
PRODUCER BYEON EUN-A

02:49.460 --> 02:51.588
Hey, Eun-a's calling. I have to go.

02:56.175 --> 02:57.135
Oh jeez.

02:59.345 --> 03:00.471
Hello, Eun-a.

03:00.555 --> 03:01.806
Director Lee.

03:03.516 --> 03:04.392
It's a good read.

03:07.020 --> 03:08.021
I'm so relieved.

03:09.188 --> 03:10.481
I was really worried.

03:11.900 --> 03:14.861
Eun-a, you're still at work, right?

03:14.944 --> 03:16.446
Would you like to have dinner?

03:16.529 --> 03:18.197
I already have plans tonight,

03:18.281 --> 03:20.116
so I'll email you my notes.

03:35.965 --> 03:37.592
How are you feeling these days?

03:39.093 --> 03:39.969
These days?

03:41.095 --> 03:42.013
I'm okay.

03:44.807 --> 03:46.976
Doesn't it all show up in the data anyway?

04:00.907 --> 04:02.408
Sometimes,

04:02.492 --> 04:06.829
what the data shows doesn't match
how participants say they feel.

04:06.913 --> 04:08.915
Can you tell me
how you're feeling right now?

04:10.333 --> 04:12.877
-Excuse me?
-How are you feeling right now?

04:13.461 --> 04:14.545
I feel okay.

04:17.006 --> 04:19.592
ANXIOUS

04:36.776 --> 04:37.777
Ms. Byeon Eun-a.

04:41.114 --> 04:42.115
This way, please.

04:43.533 --> 04:46.536
I wanted to tell you something.

04:48.913 --> 04:52.417
We've found another person who shares
the same "unknown" emotion pattern as you.

04:56.337 --> 04:57.463
Right here.

04:58.923 --> 05:01.968
The emotional profile matches
what you show when you get a nosebleed.

05:29.662 --> 05:32.915
We've only detected it once,
so we'll need to monitor it a bit more.

05:32.999 --> 05:35.835
But in any case, there's someone else.

05:57.523 --> 05:58.775
There's even an "unknown"?

05:59.358 --> 06:00.735
Apparently, there are about 20 emotions

06:01.444 --> 06:03.780
they haven't figured out what to call yet.

06:05.823 --> 06:09.911
People who exhibit the same pattern
get together to discuss

06:10.495 --> 06:12.330
and decide what to call that emotion.

06:13.039 --> 06:14.665
That sounds like fun.

06:14.749 --> 06:16.501
I like coming up with names.

06:16.584 --> 06:18.544
I hope "unknown" shows up on mine too.

06:21.172 --> 06:24.175
When does "unknown" appear for you, Eun-a?

06:27.512 --> 06:28.846
When I get nosebleeds.

06:34.602 --> 06:36.312
When I feel overwhelming rage,

06:37.396 --> 06:38.272
despair,

06:39.899 --> 06:41.943
and helplessness beyond my control.

06:43.277 --> 06:44.403
That's when I get nosebleeds.

06:46.322 --> 06:47.907
Isn't that just high blood pressure?

06:52.954 --> 06:54.705
I wonder what kind of emotion that is.

06:55.373 --> 06:56.791
What do you want to call it?

07:01.129 --> 07:02.380
"Self-destructive."

07:13.558 --> 07:14.642
For some reason,

07:15.309 --> 07:17.353
that sounds scarier than "hungry."

07:18.396 --> 07:19.230
It shows "hungry" too?

07:20.231 --> 07:21.482
It sure does.

07:21.566 --> 07:23.401
But that's not even an emotion.

07:23.484 --> 07:24.485
It doesn't seem so, right?

07:25.194 --> 07:26.863
But it was the perfect word at the time.

07:27.488 --> 07:28.906
That's when I was blown away.

07:28.990 --> 07:31.117
Whoever named it "hungry"
deserves a medal.

07:31.200 --> 07:34.287
I was hurting badly, but even then,
I was very impressed.

07:34.912 --> 07:36.164
"Hungry"?

07:36.247 --> 07:37.790
What a great name for it.

07:38.875 --> 07:42.753
You see, I'm crazy about people
who have a way with words.

07:43.504 --> 07:45.381
My brother used to write poetry.

07:46.007 --> 07:47.675
He'd always say
there are two types of writers.

07:47.758 --> 07:50.970
Those who've read the entire dictionary
at least once and those who haven't.

07:51.637 --> 07:53.264
My brother read it three times.

07:53.347 --> 07:54.182
Wow.

07:54.265 --> 07:56.726
He eventually created his own dictionary.

07:57.393 --> 08:01.564
He was passionate about using words
to find the truth.

08:02.773 --> 08:04.025
What does he do now?

08:06.027 --> 08:07.028
Well…

08:07.862 --> 08:08.821
I guess

08:09.989 --> 08:13.075
he's welding and drinking,

08:14.410 --> 08:16.037
while still looking for the truth.

08:21.000 --> 08:23.002
A wanted poster
is better than a memorial photo.

08:24.378 --> 08:25.588
So attack, don't self-destruct.

08:26.380 --> 08:27.215
Attack.

08:29.091 --> 08:29.967
Attack.

08:41.896 --> 08:43.147
For as long as I can remember,

08:43.898 --> 08:45.983
I've never seen people as just people.

08:47.818 --> 08:49.070
I saw them as masses.

08:50.279 --> 08:51.239
Masses of emotion.

08:51.822 --> 08:54.033
Wow, I like that.

08:54.700 --> 08:55.618
"Masses of emotion."

08:57.411 --> 08:59.789
It's like a person
isn't made of flesh and blood.

09:00.665 --> 09:04.335
Instead, they're made from one emotion
that keeps building over a lifetime.

09:07.213 --> 09:08.756
I bet we can name everyone here

09:09.257 --> 09:10.967
after an emotion.

09:15.346 --> 09:16.973
-"Wary."
-Right.

09:17.473 --> 09:18.516
"Pretentious."

09:19.392 --> 09:20.518
"Arrogant."

09:26.857 --> 09:27.900
"Antsy."

09:28.651 --> 09:29.485
"Resentful."

09:30.236 --> 09:31.070
"Bored."

09:34.907 --> 09:36.117
They really are

09:37.159 --> 09:38.244
all masses of emotion.

09:38.828 --> 09:40.746
There aren't many good masses of emotion.

09:42.248 --> 09:43.791
I've always wondered

09:43.874 --> 09:46.794
why people on the subway look so ugly.

09:46.877 --> 09:49.130
But I guess it wasn't their faces.

09:49.714 --> 09:51.716
It was their emotions that were ugly.

09:52.925 --> 09:54.093
You know why kids are cute?

09:54.802 --> 09:56.262
Because their emotions haven't formed yet.

09:56.929 --> 09:58.014
I see.

09:59.140 --> 10:00.016
Then what about me?

10:00.641 --> 10:01.976
What kind of mass do I look like?

10:04.228 --> 10:06.355
Just say the first thing
that comes to mind.

10:06.439 --> 10:07.273
Don't change it.

10:12.028 --> 10:12.862
"Anxious."

10:20.870 --> 10:21.704
You got me.

10:22.955 --> 10:23.956
I'm anxious.

10:25.541 --> 10:28.210
But isn't anxiety
just part of human nature?

10:29.003 --> 10:31.631
We exist as separate individuals,

10:31.714 --> 10:33.507
so how can we not feel anxious?

10:35.176 --> 10:36.969
My favorite word is

10:37.553 --> 10:38.512
"serenity."

10:39.388 --> 10:41.432
Calm and peaceful.

10:42.433 --> 10:44.226
I've never felt it before,

10:44.852 --> 10:47.104
but I have an idea of what it's like.

10:47.688 --> 10:49.482
It's a very safe

10:50.775 --> 10:52.276
and very warm feeling.

10:54.362 --> 10:58.991
Like eating tangerines under a blanket
in winter, while reading comic books,

10:59.659 --> 11:01.619
but a million times better.

11:03.287 --> 11:05.039
I'm freaking talkative, you see.

11:05.122 --> 11:06.457
You know why?

11:06.540 --> 11:10.586
Whenever I feel a rush of anxiety
charging in all of a sudden,

11:10.670 --> 11:13.589
I get loud and talk my head off

11:13.673 --> 11:14.757
to chase it away.

11:16.217 --> 11:17.385
I'm afraid of silence.

11:18.094 --> 11:19.303
I'm afraid

11:20.012 --> 11:21.889
the truth might pop out of nowhere
in the silence.

11:22.848 --> 11:23.682
Like boom.

11:27.478 --> 11:29.063
What kind of truth?

11:39.198 --> 11:40.658
When it's quiet…

11:44.495 --> 11:46.580
I feel like a Gollum-like demon
will appear…

11:48.999 --> 11:50.751
and whisper in my ear.

11:53.170 --> 11:54.004
You…

11:54.839 --> 11:56.924
are worthless.

12:01.429 --> 12:02.304
"You…

12:04.432 --> 12:05.724
are worthless."

12:59.111 --> 13:00.905
I don't usually watch

13:01.697 --> 13:02.865
my own films.

13:04.909 --> 13:06.869
Maybe "I can't" would be more accurate.

13:06.952 --> 13:08.454
Because I think I did it all wrong.

13:10.915 --> 13:13.792
But this time,
the original novel was so good

13:13.876 --> 13:15.503
that there was no way to get it wrong.

13:17.546 --> 13:21.634
I thought, "I've finally made a film
my daughter would be proud of."

13:25.429 --> 13:26.430
Q&amp;A SCREENING

13:26.514 --> 13:28.724
Before being her mom,
as an experienced actress,

13:29.517 --> 13:31.727
I've always had that kind of thirst.

13:38.651 --> 13:40.653
Mr. Choi invited us for drinks at Agit.

13:40.736 --> 13:42.112
He says it's his treat.

13:42.196 --> 13:44.198
The man is just ecstatic.

13:44.281 --> 13:45.908
We hit a million in record time,

13:45.991 --> 13:48.202
and now, he's already excited
about hitting ten million.

13:49.828 --> 13:50.788
You're coming, right?

13:52.289 --> 13:55.417
I have plans at this restaurant
I waited two months to get into.

13:55.501 --> 13:58.504
I didn't think you were the type
to wait like that, Mi-ran.

13:59.129 --> 14:00.798
I'm serious when it comes to food.

14:02.883 --> 14:05.135
Why don't we go for a drink?
Mr. Choi will be waiting.

14:05.219 --> 14:07.555
Don't say you're "serious"
about something.

14:08.639 --> 14:10.391
Just say, "I like food."

14:10.474 --> 14:12.268
That sounds much more genuine.

14:13.978 --> 14:18.148
Using trendy phrases
and trying to be "hip," as you call it,

14:18.774 --> 14:19.942
isn't hip at all.

14:21.277 --> 14:24.488
Politicians and actors
who lack their own style of expression

14:25.072 --> 14:26.115
never last long.

14:28.409 --> 14:30.119
-Let's have drinks some other time.
-Yes, ma'am.

14:40.254 --> 14:42.006
-I'll see you at home.
-Take care.

14:55.936 --> 14:57.688
-Good job.
-Nice work, everyone.

14:58.564 --> 15:00.274
Stop looking at your phone.

15:00.900 --> 15:01.817
Are you that happy?

15:03.694 --> 15:06.155
You can almost smell success
in the numbers.

15:07.239 --> 15:08.657
Check out the advance ticket sales.

15:08.741 --> 15:10.242
MY MOTHER
ADVANCE TICKET SALES: 65.8%

15:10.326 --> 15:12.536
It's been so long
since I've seen numbers like this.

15:13.162 --> 15:13.996
All right.

15:14.747 --> 15:18.000
The mom stepped in to fix
what her daughter botched up.

15:18.626 --> 15:20.252
Sorry for botching things up.

15:20.336 --> 15:21.670
Come on, that's how it is.

15:21.754 --> 15:24.173
You tank ten before you land one.

15:24.256 --> 15:25.090
You know this.

15:25.174 --> 15:26.926
I wonder when I'll finally land that one.

15:27.968 --> 15:29.595
Just stay right by my side.

15:29.678 --> 15:31.764
As long as you're with me,
you'll land at least one.

15:32.556 --> 15:33.724
We're doing this.

15:34.391 --> 15:36.393
Here's to hitting ten million!

15:36.477 --> 15:37.311
Let's go!

15:37.394 --> 15:39.146
-Let's go!
-Let's go!

15:43.525 --> 15:44.860
What's Director Park Gyeong-se doing?

15:44.944 --> 15:46.403
Tell him to come for a drink.

15:46.487 --> 15:48.739
Just leave him alone.
He's not in a good place these days.

15:48.822 --> 15:50.658
DECISION TO STAY

17:19.329 --> 17:21.623
Get some rest on your days off!

17:21.707 --> 17:23.208
Don't just drink!

17:51.487 --> 17:52.863
THE EIGHT CLUB

17:53.947 --> 17:55.449
Read this, Hwang Dong-man.

17:56.075 --> 17:58.410
We live in an era
where people leave comments

17:58.494 --> 18:01.622
like mutts leaving crap wherever they go.

18:02.414 --> 18:05.334
We see your crap every single day.

18:05.417 --> 18:08.420
Our group chat is filled with your crap.

18:09.004 --> 18:11.423
You're supposed to clean up
your own crap, you know.

18:12.007 --> 18:16.637
Whenever I think of you,
I feel nothing but rage all day

18:16.720 --> 18:20.933
because of all the crap
you've written and said so far.

18:21.934 --> 18:25.020
Every day, I think about the things
I didn't get to say to you that day.

18:26.021 --> 18:27.648
"I should've said that."

18:27.731 --> 18:29.233
"I should've said that too."

18:29.316 --> 18:31.485
After a sleepless, rage-filled night,

18:31.568 --> 18:35.155
I've decided to sit down
and organize my thoughts clearly.

18:36.657 --> 18:38.617
I want you to read this out loud

18:39.326 --> 18:41.495
the same way I did.

18:41.578 --> 18:43.539
I want you to swallow these words

18:44.164 --> 18:45.916
the same way I did.

18:46.583 --> 18:47.626
And I hope it hurts.

18:48.335 --> 18:49.753
I hope it hurts

18:49.837 --> 18:52.673
when you read this and choke it down.

18:52.756 --> 18:54.174
No vegetables today?

18:58.178 --> 18:59.012
One.

18:59.888 --> 19:02.850
When the whole country
raved about Ki-ri's drama,

19:02.933 --> 19:05.227
you refused to watch it
even though he's your friend.

19:05.310 --> 19:06.645
Then you said,

19:06.728 --> 19:10.023
"For some reason,
I'm not into things everyone else likes."

19:10.107 --> 19:11.441
"This is why I haven't made it yet."

19:11.525 --> 19:12.651
"I'm just too niche."

19:12.734 --> 19:14.319
This is why I haven't made it yet.

19:14.403 --> 19:15.362
I'm just too niche.

19:16.989 --> 19:19.158
Do you remember the vibe in the room
when you said that?

19:19.867 --> 19:21.743
Everyone went quiet.

19:22.744 --> 19:24.663
Why do you think we stopped talking?

19:25.289 --> 19:27.624
Because we were pissed off.

19:28.542 --> 19:30.127
You know why you're not successful.

19:30.210 --> 19:32.546
I know. We all know.

19:33.088 --> 19:36.091
But seeing you
try to one-up whoever's in front of you

19:36.175 --> 19:38.510
just freaking pissed us off.

19:38.594 --> 19:41.138
Want me to run through
all the masters of niche cinema?

19:41.221 --> 19:44.224
Or how about a list
of successful niche film directors?

19:44.308 --> 19:46.560
Being niche isn't why you haven't made it.

19:47.186 --> 19:48.854
You just have no talent.

19:48.937 --> 19:50.147
Your work is boring!

19:58.113 --> 19:59.406
Damn it!

20:07.414 --> 20:09.666
I WANT YOU TO READ THIS OUT LOUD,
THE SAME WAY I DID…

20:16.423 --> 20:18.467
He really went there, didn't he?

20:18.550 --> 20:19.426
No way.

20:20.636 --> 20:23.388
I bet Hwang Dong-man
wants to die right now.

20:23.472 --> 20:24.473
What is it?

20:27.309 --> 20:28.227
No way.

20:39.529 --> 20:41.073
They look real.

20:41.156 --> 20:42.532
It has an amazing grip.

20:43.659 --> 20:45.244
It's just like a real gun.

20:49.581 --> 20:51.083
What's the movie about?

20:51.959 --> 20:55.796
Public officials who take care of people
who stress out citizens.

20:56.755 --> 20:59.758
Sounds like a lot of politicians
will get killed.

21:05.180 --> 21:07.057
Click, clack.

21:08.100 --> 21:09.142
Bang!

21:10.310 --> 21:13.438
This only has two loading steps,
so it doesn't sound as good.

21:14.481 --> 21:17.234
If you're going to kill someone,
you might as well use something cathartic.

21:18.777 --> 21:21.196
Click, click, clack, thunk!

21:21.280 --> 21:22.698
Bang!

21:23.282 --> 21:25.534
You need at least four loading steps

21:25.617 --> 21:29.246
to boost the action
and make the audience's hearts pound.

21:29.329 --> 21:31.331
Can't we use real guns?

21:32.249 --> 21:34.751
We can, but it's a headache.

21:34.835 --> 21:38.338
The firearms supplier drops them off
at the police station on filming day.

21:38.422 --> 21:41.174
The production company has to pick them up

21:41.258 --> 21:43.593
and then return them exactly on time,

21:43.677 --> 21:45.095
so it's better not to use them.

21:45.595 --> 21:48.890
Come on, these look and feel
just like real guns!

21:51.518 --> 21:53.937
See? You tried to dodge it.

21:57.566 --> 21:58.567
Amazing, right?

22:28.805 --> 22:29.848
Two.

22:31.850 --> 22:36.646
On the FAM tour, you had the nerve
to ask a famous director for their name.

22:37.397 --> 22:39.357
The way you pretended not to know someone

22:39.441 --> 22:42.652
who clearly had no reason to know you
was sheer arrogance.

22:42.736 --> 22:44.696
Everyone else just stayed quiet
the whole trip,

22:44.780 --> 22:47.866
but you couldn't stop talking
because you were busy hiding

22:47.949 --> 22:49.826
the fact that you were a nobody!

22:49.910 --> 22:54.498
You talked your head off
like your life depended on it!

22:55.874 --> 22:59.002
In the end, you proved to everyone
that you were a nobody!

22:59.086 --> 23:02.005
That's why we never
go on FAM tours with you anymore.

23:05.050 --> 23:06.593
Because there's no reason

23:08.178 --> 23:10.806
to put up with your crap in public.

23:13.850 --> 23:14.810
Three.

23:15.727 --> 23:19.397
You keep getting rejected,
but you do it again

23:19.981 --> 23:21.608
-and again.
-Mr. Hwang Dong-man?

23:21.691 --> 23:22.526
Yes?

23:27.864 --> 23:28.907
Back to three.

23:30.200 --> 23:33.203
You keep getting rejected,
but you do it again

23:34.162 --> 23:34.996
and again.

23:35.664 --> 23:37.541
You refuse to give up.

23:37.624 --> 23:39.334
Now it makes me wonder,

23:41.002 --> 23:43.130
"Maybe he's hoping he can keep doing this

23:44.047 --> 23:45.549
until the day he dies."

23:53.807 --> 23:55.725
Hello, it's good to see you here.

24:05.986 --> 24:07.904
Hwang Dong-man, did you read it?

24:10.407 --> 24:11.908
I know you can hear me!

24:16.204 --> 24:17.622
Read it out loud!

24:18.123 --> 24:21.209
Choke down every single word, all right?

24:23.086 --> 24:25.172
That dumbass can't even act.

24:25.922 --> 24:27.340
Come on, that's enough.

24:33.680 --> 24:34.890
What's wrong?

24:34.973 --> 24:36.808
Hwang Dong-man just walked by.

24:36.892 --> 24:37.809
Really?

24:40.061 --> 24:41.396
That bastard didn't even read it.

24:42.898 --> 24:44.065
I guarantee it.

24:45.150 --> 24:46.318
But the unread count is zero.

24:46.401 --> 24:48.320
He just cleared the count
but didn't actually read it.

24:49.112 --> 24:51.656
What's the root of all mental illnesses?

24:52.282 --> 24:53.408
Refusing to face reality.

24:53.491 --> 24:55.076
It'd kill him if he read it.

24:55.160 --> 24:56.328
He won't read it.

24:56.411 --> 24:57.370
He can't!

24:57.871 --> 24:59.289
He's always been like that.

24:59.372 --> 25:01.166
Whenever anyone hits him with the truth,

25:03.335 --> 25:04.211
he doesn't listen.

25:04.294 --> 25:06.421
It's meant to hurt him like hell,

25:06.504 --> 25:09.257
but the idiot just laughs
and rambles about something else.

25:09.341 --> 25:10.884
Gyeong-se,

25:10.967 --> 25:12.636
you took a crap in the group chat too.

25:12.719 --> 25:14.179
I know I did!

25:14.763 --> 25:17.641
I wanted to show him
he's not the only one who can take a crap.

25:17.724 --> 25:20.769
Jun-hwan says he'll get better
after wearing the emotion watch.

25:20.852 --> 25:24.064
Tell that asshole to take some damn meds
instead of wearing that stupid watch!

25:33.031 --> 25:34.241
What just happened?

25:46.628 --> 25:48.171
Damn it!

25:49.839 --> 25:51.258
Are you kidding me?

25:51.341 --> 25:53.218
-Hey, Gyeong-se!
-That little…

25:53.301 --> 25:54.636
Where are you going?

25:55.262 --> 25:56.221
Damn it.

26:40.015 --> 26:41.308
I can't even finish reading it.

26:44.269 --> 26:46.271
There's something I didn't tell you.

26:49.607 --> 26:50.817
If you scroll up,

26:52.235 --> 26:55.405
you'll see all the crap
that bastard wrote about me.

26:55.488 --> 26:56.323
Why do you think I--

26:56.406 --> 26:57.699
Cham, cham, cham.

27:01.953 --> 27:04.205
Why do you think
I was so harsh on Dong-man

27:04.289 --> 27:05.498
and banned him from here?

27:06.207 --> 27:08.168
Because I couldn't stand him?

27:08.752 --> 27:12.339
It's because I'm embarrassed
by how you lose your shit around him!

27:13.131 --> 27:15.300
One word from him,
and you shake with rage!

27:16.259 --> 27:17.886
Aren't you ashamed to face your juniors?

27:18.636 --> 27:20.347
What about our staff?

27:21.514 --> 27:23.058
If you do this one more time,

27:23.141 --> 27:24.642
I'll take down
the "Hwang Dong-man not allowed" sign

27:24.726 --> 27:26.978
and put up one that says
"Park Gyeong-se not allowed."

27:33.234 --> 27:34.152
Damn it.

27:44.162 --> 27:46.206
I think we'll hit ten million
in record time.

27:49.292 --> 27:52.545
I can probably quit right now
and live off this for the rest of my life.

27:52.629 --> 27:53.963
But you know how it is.

27:54.047 --> 27:55.173
I'll just use that money for a new film.

27:58.885 --> 28:00.261
Excuse me, sir.

28:00.345 --> 28:02.138
Something weird just came up.

28:03.223 --> 28:04.974
I think you should see this.

28:05.058 --> 28:07.560
Hey, I'll call you back later.

28:07.644 --> 28:08.645
Okay.

28:10.897 --> 28:11.940
Something weird?

28:13.108 --> 28:14.067
What is it?

28:19.197 --> 28:22.033
"It bothers me
to see her with Jang Mi-ran…"

28:32.168 --> 28:34.796
IT BOTHERS ME TO SEE HER WITH JANG MI-RAN,
ACTING LIKE A LOVING MOTHER AND DAUGHTER

28:34.879 --> 28:35.964
WHEN THEY AREN'T EVEN RELATED

28:39.092 --> 28:40.176
When was this posted?

28:42.762 --> 28:43.680
Huh?

28:43.763 --> 28:45.056
It's me.

28:45.140 --> 28:46.224
Did you see the social media post?

28:48.476 --> 28:49.477
What is it?

28:59.154 --> 29:01.239
"It bothers me
to see her with Jang Mi-ran,

29:01.322 --> 29:04.075
acting like a loving mother and daughter

29:05.076 --> 29:06.327
when they aren't even related."

29:07.620 --> 29:09.289
"I still remember that girl

29:09.372 --> 29:11.374
from elementary school 23 years ago."

29:12.167 --> 29:14.169
"Last name Byeon.'"

29:16.838 --> 29:18.423
"She's Oh Jeong-hui's daughter,

29:18.506 --> 29:20.467
but she was neglected and grew up

29:21.134 --> 29:22.761
without her parents."

29:25.138 --> 29:27.640
"Oh Jeong-hui
was an unknown actor back then,

29:27.724 --> 29:31.603
but she looked too elegant
to live in our shabby neighborhood."

29:31.686 --> 29:33.563
"That's why I remember her name."

29:35.482 --> 29:38.651
"Compared to Oh Jeong-hui,
her daughter was quiet and ordinary."

29:39.527 --> 29:42.822
"I didn't think much of it at the time,
but looking back now,

29:42.906 --> 29:44.908
my heart simply goes out to her."

29:46.159 --> 29:48.328
"I wonder what she's doing now

29:49.537 --> 29:51.456
and how her life is going."

29:52.707 --> 29:54.542
Just stop, will you?

29:54.626 --> 29:56.878
You're not fed up with the film industry
that's starving your family,

29:56.961 --> 29:58.671
but you're fed up with me?

29:58.755 --> 30:01.591
You miss that hellhole so much?

30:03.176 --> 30:04.969
One day, my dad left.

30:10.183 --> 30:11.726
Then, my mom left.

30:16.856 --> 30:19.025
I went to school like nothing happened,

30:20.401 --> 30:24.072
even though my heart was pounding so hard,
I thought it'd pop out of my chest.

30:25.365 --> 30:27.200
I went to school like nothing happened,

30:28.159 --> 30:29.244
ate alone…

30:31.287 --> 30:32.330
and slept alone.

30:37.001 --> 30:38.795
Why didn't you tell anyone?

30:40.255 --> 30:43.007
You could've told your teacher
that you were alone.

30:48.388 --> 30:49.973
Did you think it might put you in danger?

30:51.850 --> 30:52.767
No.

30:56.312 --> 30:58.314
I couldn't let anyone find out
I'd been abandoned.

31:16.124 --> 31:18.334
One word from the daughter,
and it'll be over.

31:18.418 --> 31:20.336
"It's not true. I was never neglected."

31:20.420 --> 31:23.590
Why go overboard
and issue an official statement?

31:24.632 --> 31:28.094
People know Oh Jeong-hui
got divorced at a young age.

31:28.177 --> 31:30.805
Her husband raised their kid.
She wasn't neglected.

31:30.889 --> 31:32.098
That's her side of the story.

31:32.181 --> 31:33.474
The truth doesn't matter right now.

31:33.558 --> 31:36.019
What matters
is making it look like the truth!

31:36.102 --> 31:39.564
It'll only look like the truth
if the daughter says it herself.

31:39.647 --> 31:42.317
Oh Jeong-hui can talk all she wants,
but no one will believe her.

31:42.400 --> 31:45.737
How can she ask her daughter
if she can't get in touch with her?

31:46.487 --> 31:48.531
What do you mean
she can't get in touch with her?

31:49.365 --> 31:52.785
You know this is a bad sign, right?

31:52.869 --> 31:55.455
Never mind My Mother tanking
right before hitting ten million.

31:55.538 --> 31:59.918
One wrong move and Oh Jeong-hui
can kiss her career goodbye.

32:02.545 --> 32:04.255
Okay, fine. Go ahead.

32:04.339 --> 32:06.215
Issue an official statement for now.

32:08.134 --> 32:09.344
But make it sound really sad.

32:09.427 --> 32:11.638
No, heartbreaking. You know what I mean.

32:11.721 --> 32:13.264
"I worried about her my whole life."

32:13.348 --> 32:14.599
"We got divorced when she was little,

32:14.682 --> 32:17.018
but I did the best I could
while raising her."

32:17.101 --> 32:19.562
Write something along those lines,
and show it to her.

32:19.646 --> 32:23.107
Ask her if it's okay
to issue such a statement.

32:23.733 --> 32:26.277
She'll know whether it's okay or not.

32:28.905 --> 32:30.657
If you issue it without thinking,

32:30.740 --> 32:32.617
and the daughter comes forward
claiming she was neglected,

32:32.700 --> 32:34.535
Oh Jeong-hui's career will be over.

32:34.619 --> 32:35.870
So just ask her, damn it!

32:41.417 --> 32:42.502
And one more thing, Mr. Park.

32:43.795 --> 32:45.088
Find the daughter.

32:46.005 --> 32:47.548
Find her!

32:47.632 --> 32:50.301
We need to find her and fix this,

32:50.385 --> 32:52.178
even if it means making amends or begging!

32:56.265 --> 32:58.393
DM the person who posted it.

32:58.476 --> 33:02.105
Tell them to take it down, or we'll sue
for spreading false information.

33:02.188 --> 33:03.231
Intimidate them a bit.

33:03.314 --> 33:04.565
-Got it?
-Yes, sir.

33:05.608 --> 33:06.484
Damn it!

33:22.166 --> 33:23.668
She left her husband and child,

33:25.294 --> 33:27.839
who weren't good enough for her…

33:30.174 --> 33:33.636
and replaced them
with a shiny new husband and child.

33:36.639 --> 33:39.183
There really are people
who get everything they want.

33:53.573 --> 33:56.284
When depression pressed down on me
like a heavy iron weight,

33:56.367 --> 33:58.161
and I couldn't even sit up,

33:59.078 --> 34:00.413
all I wanted…

34:01.456 --> 34:02.623
was weather.

34:04.333 --> 34:06.169
If it were a warm, spring day…

34:07.253 --> 34:09.005
If cherry blossoms were in the air…

34:10.339 --> 34:14.594
I'd read Park Gyeong-se's message
as if it were a love letter.

34:56.427 --> 34:57.261
"Don't take this…"

34:57.345 --> 35:02.266
Don't take this as me trying to tell you
to get your act together.

35:03.101 --> 35:06.687
At this point,
I'd feel even more bitter and resentful

35:06.771 --> 35:08.981
if I thought
you'd finally gotten your life together.

35:10.441 --> 35:14.320
I think the only way
I could die in peace is to know

35:14.904 --> 35:16.531
you're still exactly where you are
right now.

35:17.490 --> 35:23.329
So please keep living the way
you always have until the very end.

35:24.997 --> 35:28.876
"Keep living the way you always have
until the very end."

35:30.169 --> 35:31.087
Seven.

35:32.046 --> 35:33.005
Goddamn it.

35:33.673 --> 35:35.216
Why the hell is it so long?

35:35.716 --> 35:38.386
He talked about dying,
so this should be the end.

35:46.060 --> 35:48.271
A SCARY WOMAN
BY LEE JUN-HWAN

35:49.605 --> 35:50.481
You know,

35:51.607 --> 35:54.777
I believed you when you said
you'd really go mainstream this time.

35:55.528 --> 35:56.696
When I read the first draft,

35:57.446 --> 36:00.116
I thought,
"He worked really hard on this."

36:00.741 --> 36:03.786
"A bit more effort
would definitely make it mainstream."

36:04.996 --> 36:11.085
So tell me why I'm seeing your signature
B-movie vibes in the revised draft.

36:12.003 --> 36:13.212
One thing's for sure.

36:14.380 --> 36:16.382
You think there's an actor

36:16.966 --> 36:17.842
who'd do this?

36:17.925 --> 36:20.011
No, not among A-listers.

36:20.636 --> 36:23.139
Are you going to make another film
with a B-lister

36:23.222 --> 36:24.849
and take pride in simply having made it?

36:24.932 --> 36:26.934
You said you wouldn't do that anymore.

36:27.018 --> 36:30.271
That's what you promised me
when you signed the contract.

36:30.354 --> 36:33.357
You might feel this way
because the character stands out,

36:34.400 --> 36:35.943
but it doesn't have B-movie vibes.

36:36.736 --> 36:39.113
Even Eun-a said the revised draft
was much better.

36:45.453 --> 36:47.997
So if Byeon Eun-a likes it,
does it mean it's good?

36:49.332 --> 36:52.001
Why do you all keep saying,
"But Byeon Eun-a liked it"?

36:52.084 --> 36:53.169
Is she always right?

36:53.252 --> 36:55.129
You keep singing praises about her.

36:55.213 --> 36:57.089
Haven't you guys on the second floor heard

36:58.007 --> 37:00.009
I've been giving her a freaking hard time?

37:00.718 --> 37:02.053
You want to get kicked out of your office?

37:02.553 --> 37:04.972
Eun-a reads screenplays objectively

37:05.056 --> 37:06.432
without picturing specific actors.

37:06.515 --> 37:08.976
You have to read them
with specific actors in mind!

37:09.810 --> 37:10.686
It makes sense now.

37:11.938 --> 37:14.857
I was so frustrated reading this
because I couldn't imagine the cast.

37:20.738 --> 37:21.614
Ax, get in here.

37:25.451 --> 37:27.912
Ax, my ass. She can't even hit the mark.

37:29.455 --> 37:30.289
I said get in here!

37:42.468 --> 37:44.136
I heard you said this was good.

37:45.429 --> 37:47.181
Who should we cast for this?

37:47.265 --> 37:48.724
Give me some names.

37:54.939 --> 37:56.190
Come on.

37:57.316 --> 37:58.192
Jang Mi-ran.

37:58.276 --> 38:00.736
Why would she agree to this
unless she wants to end her career?

38:01.654 --> 38:03.406
Will you cast her yourself?

38:04.573 --> 38:07.076
You need to think about the casting
when you read.

38:07.159 --> 38:08.995
If you like it, that's all?

38:09.078 --> 38:10.413
Are we publishing this as a book?

38:10.496 --> 38:11.747
Are we a publisher now?

38:12.456 --> 38:14.792
How frustrating.

38:25.678 --> 38:27.888
I'm sorry.
I should've persuaded him better.

38:29.181 --> 38:30.308
It's okay.

38:32.310 --> 38:33.853
I agree that the revised draft is better.

38:35.730 --> 38:37.857
If we can't trust our own instincts,
who can we trust?

38:51.037 --> 38:53.164
Hwang Dong-man has been messaging you.

38:56.500 --> 38:58.544
You two must be getting close.

38:58.627 --> 39:01.505
What, are you really going to see
for yourself what he's like?

39:04.550 --> 39:05.760
Aren't you embarrassed by him?

39:15.561 --> 39:17.521
I'm more embarrassed for you,
saying something like that.

39:30.618 --> 39:31.619
I just wish

39:33.371 --> 39:35.998
you'd give up and leave the film industry.

39:37.375 --> 39:40.961
Don't kid yourself into thinking
that you're actually talented

39:41.587 --> 39:44.340
just because you shone briefly.

39:45.007 --> 39:48.302
Or else you'll end up like Hwang Dong-man
with 20 years down the drain.

40:11.700 --> 40:12.743
Delivery!

40:25.631 --> 40:26.715
That'll be 28,000 won.

40:27.967 --> 40:29.135
Food's here.

40:36.809 --> 40:38.018
I said the food's here.

40:48.737 --> 40:49.572
Hey.

40:58.914 --> 41:00.833
-How much?
-It's 28,000 won.

41:07.298 --> 41:08.382
-Enjoy your food.
-Thank you.

42:22.706 --> 42:23.707
MS. BYEON EUN-A

42:27.878 --> 42:29.421
What made you call me at this hour?

42:32.132 --> 42:33.801
Tell me a funny story.

42:36.554 --> 42:37.429
Do you have

42:38.055 --> 42:39.056
a sixth sense?

42:39.682 --> 42:40.766
How did you know to call?

42:41.892 --> 42:44.562
I had a really weird experience just now.

42:45.229 --> 42:47.398
I ordered delivery and was lying down,

42:47.481 --> 42:48.607
but I didn't fall asleep.

42:48.691 --> 42:50.901
I could hear my brother moving around.

42:51.527 --> 42:52.653
Then suddenly,

42:53.404 --> 42:56.115
my brother got on top of my back

42:56.198 --> 42:58.993
and started stomping on me.

42:59.076 --> 43:00.828
I thought he had lost his mind.

43:00.911 --> 43:03.205
I was sleepy and annoyed,

43:03.289 --> 43:04.623
but too lazy to get up.

43:05.457 --> 43:06.333
But then

43:07.126 --> 43:09.920
I heard him grab a bottle of alcohol
from across the room.

43:17.845 --> 43:20.723
So I thought,
"Then who's on my back right now?"

43:22.349 --> 43:23.267
It's sleep paralysis.

43:23.851 --> 43:26.937
That's when I thought I might die,

43:27.021 --> 43:29.189
but I couldn't even move a finger.

43:29.273 --> 43:30.441
You know how it is.

43:30.524 --> 43:32.526
You can't move an inch,
no matter how hard you try.

43:33.527 --> 43:37.114
This bastard was dancing on my back,
and I'm losing my mind.

43:38.157 --> 43:38.991
Just then…

43:40.409 --> 43:41.493
Delivery!

43:42.411 --> 43:43.454
I thought, "Yes, I'm saved!"

43:44.330 --> 43:45.414
Food's here.

43:45.497 --> 43:47.541
"Please kick me."

43:47.625 --> 43:49.043
I said the food's here.

43:49.126 --> 43:51.378
"Come on, just kick me!"

43:51.462 --> 43:52.713
"As hard as you can!"

43:53.964 --> 43:56.008
"Yes, that's right."

43:56.091 --> 43:56.925
"Come on."

43:58.427 --> 44:00.262
-Hey.
-"Just kick me, you bastard!"

44:00.346 --> 44:01.680
"Please!"

44:05.809 --> 44:07.603
-"Damn it."
-It's 28,000 won.

44:10.064 --> 44:12.066
I felt like I was dying,

44:12.149 --> 44:14.193
but he just kept drinking.

44:14.276 --> 44:16.737
It made me feel sad all of a sudden.

44:16.820 --> 44:19.657
"I've got enough people to fight,
and now I have to fight sleep paralysis?"

44:20.783 --> 44:22.993
"Forget it. I'm not going to fight it."

44:23.077 --> 44:25.704
"Go ahead and beat me, sleep paralysis."

44:25.788 --> 44:27.247
"It's not like I'm going to die."

44:28.123 --> 44:29.083
You know what I mean.

44:29.166 --> 44:32.586
It feels like you're going to die,
but you don't actually die.

44:33.337 --> 44:35.798
"So go ahead, sleep paralysis. You win."

44:36.965 --> 44:39.760
"Stomp on me or smother me.
Do whatever you want."

44:39.843 --> 44:43.055
"I'll just imagine being under a blanket,
eating tangerines in winter."

44:43.889 --> 44:45.849
And I just kept still.

44:46.433 --> 44:47.559
The weird thing was…

44:49.770 --> 44:52.147
once I started ignoring it,

44:52.231 --> 44:54.274
it felt like the sleep paralysis
got thrown off.

44:54.858 --> 44:56.777
I was supposed to be in pain,

44:58.028 --> 45:00.447
but when I said, "Go ahead, you win"

45:01.490 --> 45:03.075
and kept still,

45:03.992 --> 45:05.411
it was almost like it lost steam

45:06.120 --> 45:09.123
and just slithered away.

45:19.925 --> 45:22.177
It felt like I learned something.

45:24.888 --> 45:29.268
Some things are worth a fight,
and some aren't.

45:29.351 --> 45:32.855
And sleep paralysis
wasn't something worth a fight.

45:43.824 --> 45:46.160
Don't fight the thing
that's giving you a hard time, Eun-a.

45:47.077 --> 45:48.245
It's like sleep paralysis.

45:49.746 --> 45:51.415
If you just ignore it, it'll pass.

45:52.541 --> 45:53.876
Just let it go on its way.

45:59.381 --> 46:01.425
I feel better now after talking.

46:02.176 --> 46:03.677
It's been hard these past few days,

46:04.553 --> 46:06.847
but this definitely proves
that talking gives me energy.

46:10.517 --> 46:12.102
What's been giving you a hard time?

46:15.063 --> 46:19.485
Well, I made it to the final round,
so I went in for the interview, but…

46:19.568 --> 46:21.320
Damn it, I always make it
to the final round.

46:22.070 --> 46:22.988
Anyway…

46:25.866 --> 46:28.368
You can tell the moment
you walk into an interview

46:28.452 --> 46:30.579
whether you've got it or not.

46:31.413 --> 46:33.916
I was thinking that I didn't get it again

46:34.625 --> 46:35.709
and just sat there.

46:36.418 --> 46:40.631
Then at the last minute,
a judge asked why I wanted to make films.

46:42.132 --> 46:43.258
She asked, and…

46:47.763 --> 46:48.597
Well…

46:50.140 --> 46:52.809
As I was answering, I got choked up.
It was humiliating.

46:55.854 --> 46:57.022
What did you say?

46:58.023 --> 46:59.858
Why do you want to make films?

47:09.243 --> 47:10.077
I want to…

47:12.204 --> 47:13.705
I want to see someone…

47:17.334 --> 47:19.211
living on the opposite side of the world…

47:29.221 --> 47:30.597
and feel that I exist there too.

47:37.187 --> 47:38.230
I just…

47:39.022 --> 47:40.649
What gets to me more than losing the grant

47:41.525 --> 47:43.610
is that I couldn't hold back my tears.

47:44.778 --> 47:46.613
That's what kills me the most.

47:49.157 --> 47:52.160
On top of that, I said…

47:54.204 --> 47:55.205
All for one…

47:56.498 --> 47:57.332
and one for all.

48:00.085 --> 48:01.503
I mean, seriously.

48:02.379 --> 48:05.507
Why did I say,
"All for one, and one for all"?

48:05.591 --> 48:08.260
What am I going to do? I'm so embarrassed.

48:31.658 --> 48:33.327
My nose stopped bleeding.

49:44.690 --> 49:47.484
Why do you have
Director Kim Hyeon-tae's screenplay

49:47.567 --> 49:49.152
when the producer in charge
hasn't even seen it yet?

49:49.778 --> 49:53.782
Don't you dare review screenplays
behind my back again.

49:56.243 --> 49:57.119
Review this.

50:18.849 --> 50:20.684
If I get choked up while writing,

50:21.935 --> 50:23.353
the audience will get choked up too.

50:23.854 --> 50:25.856
If I laugh while writing,

50:25.939 --> 50:27.524
the audience will laugh too.

50:28.316 --> 50:31.486
If I feel pain while writing,
the audience will also feel pain.

50:33.238 --> 50:35.782
Did you get choked up writing this?
Or did you laugh?

50:38.660 --> 50:41.329
Stringing letters together isn't writing.

50:41.413 --> 50:43.665
You have to make people feel something.

50:43.749 --> 50:46.251
When we were little,
we used to walk around like this.

50:47.043 --> 50:48.170
Do you remember?

50:48.253 --> 50:49.504
Do you see any adults
walking around like that?

50:50.088 --> 50:51.214
Are there any adults so happy?

50:51.298 --> 50:52.924
Nope. There aren't any.

50:53.425 --> 50:55.469
That's why they go to the movie theater.

50:56.595 --> 50:57.554
To feel.

50:58.305 --> 51:00.807
They want to get choked up,
be moved to tears,

51:00.891 --> 51:02.350
and crack up.

51:03.351 --> 51:06.313
They want to feel alive again.

51:06.396 --> 51:09.107
So don't just force a story together
with words.

51:09.191 --> 51:11.234
Kick the story into gear.

51:11.318 --> 51:12.652
Bring out people's emotions!

51:13.236 --> 51:15.489
How do you kick a story into gear?

51:19.785 --> 51:20.952
Open a thousand doors.

51:21.912 --> 51:23.663
And make your way through them.

51:24.581 --> 51:26.958
And the background music should be

51:27.584 --> 51:28.460
guitar music.

52:15.215 --> 52:19.302
"It also means facing fear and guilt."

52:19.386 --> 52:20.512
"Fear…"

52:26.685 --> 52:27.519
What is it?

52:28.603 --> 52:29.646
What do you want?

52:32.691 --> 52:36.611
I've always struggled to deal with people
who walk all over me.

52:38.113 --> 52:40.073
Should I avoid them,
or put them in their place?

52:42.367 --> 52:44.244
I always chose to avoid them.

52:45.328 --> 52:46.288
But this time,

52:47.539 --> 52:49.124
I'm going to put them in their place.

52:51.877 --> 52:55.463
I've never once thought you were powerful.

52:56.506 --> 52:58.258
I do think you're a pain in the ass.

52:59.509 --> 53:01.177
I hope you don't get those two confused.

53:01.678 --> 53:02.846
Also,

53:03.680 --> 53:05.432
I'm a quiet person,

53:06.016 --> 53:07.559
but I'm not a weak pushover.

53:08.476 --> 53:09.978
I hope you don't confuse this as well.

53:15.692 --> 53:19.529
Please don't assume I'm quitting
by pulling some stunt.

53:20.155 --> 53:21.448
I don't intend to quit.

53:33.126 --> 53:34.127
It must be entertaining,

53:35.128 --> 53:37.088
watching someone get pushed out.

53:38.381 --> 53:39.341
It is entertaining.

53:40.050 --> 53:42.010
I'll admit it
because I've felt that before too.

53:42.719 --> 53:43.595
But you know,

53:44.220 --> 53:46.222
I'd rather you be upfront about it,
like Hwang Dong-man.

53:47.933 --> 53:51.061
"It's so satisfying to see
that you've lost Mr. Choi's favor."

53:53.605 --> 53:55.315
At least that'd be amusing.

53:57.317 --> 53:58.693
What did you just say?

54:04.324 --> 54:06.368
-Hey, Ax--
-I'm taking off early.

54:08.119 --> 54:10.664
Or should I stay and endure

54:10.747 --> 54:12.165
this awkward atmosphere?

54:12.958 --> 54:14.626
I'm confident I can endure it.

54:15.627 --> 54:19.631
I've been tied to a desk since I was nine,
so I know I can handle it.

54:21.174 --> 54:22.842
But can the rest of you handle it?

54:46.658 --> 54:48.493
Is something contagious going around?

54:49.077 --> 54:50.495
Why are all these losers acting up?

54:53.081 --> 54:53.915
Where are you?

54:55.041 --> 54:56.126
Agit.

54:56.209 --> 54:57.627
We should meet. Come outside.

55:13.268 --> 55:14.310
Hey, it's Dong-man.

55:28.450 --> 55:29.784
So?

55:30.660 --> 55:32.954
Did you choke down every last word?

55:36.791 --> 55:37.709
You know,

55:38.376 --> 55:43.048
reading that out loud was so exhausting
that I ended up with sleep paralysis.

55:43.631 --> 55:48.386
Every single word
got under my skin and cut so deep,

55:49.637 --> 55:51.681
it felt like
I was getting tattooed all over.

55:54.142 --> 55:55.977
Write your screenplays like that!

55:56.061 --> 55:57.020
You asshole.

55:57.103 --> 55:58.646
-No, don't!
-Hold on.

56:00.815 --> 56:02.817
Every word was dripping with sincerity.

56:03.902 --> 56:06.529
It was the best thing
you've written so far.

56:06.613 --> 56:07.614
Write your screenplays like that!

56:07.697 --> 56:08.573
You crazy bastard!

56:08.656 --> 56:10.033
-Hold on!
-Stop!

56:11.451 --> 56:13.078
What pisses me off the most

56:13.161 --> 56:15.205
is you assuming that I'm so miserable.

56:15.830 --> 56:19.542
Things aren't working out for me,
so I should shut up and be miserable

56:19.626 --> 56:21.836
and know my place, right?

56:22.670 --> 56:25.423
Want to hear something really shocking?

56:26.341 --> 56:27.467
Guess what?

56:27.550 --> 56:30.845
I'm not as miserable
as you all think I am.

56:32.430 --> 56:36.142
I bet a pampered rich kid
can't even begin to imagine

56:36.226 --> 56:38.770
how people can live
in a basement apartment.

56:38.853 --> 56:41.231
I bet they think they're really miserable.

56:41.314 --> 56:44.776
Screw that. People who live there
laugh and have fun too.

56:44.859 --> 56:48.655
They're not pretending.
They really aren't miserable.

56:49.280 --> 56:50.323
I bet you all thought

56:50.949 --> 56:52.992
everything would be great
once you debuted.

56:53.660 --> 56:55.912
You thought it'd be
a whole new world, right?

56:56.496 --> 56:58.248
So did anything change?

56:58.331 --> 56:59.165
No, right?

56:59.249 --> 57:01.459
It's the same.

57:01.543 --> 57:05.004
After 20 years,
14 screenplays, and no debut,

57:05.088 --> 57:08.007
I'm just like the rest of you.

57:08.716 --> 57:11.052
I'm just as miserable

57:11.136 --> 57:13.471
and just as happy as the rest of you.

57:13.555 --> 57:16.933
Actually, my life could be
way more fun than yours.

57:18.226 --> 57:21.688
This is all to say
that you guys are no better than me,

57:21.771 --> 57:23.398
so stop acting so superior.

57:24.774 --> 57:28.236
Do you really believe that,
or have you completely lost your mind?

57:28.319 --> 57:29.446
Also!

57:29.529 --> 57:32.657
You say I need to talk less,
but I won't ever do that.

57:32.740 --> 57:35.034
Joking is the only thing
that makes me feel like I exist.

57:35.118 --> 57:36.578
If I stop talking, I'm dead.

57:36.661 --> 57:38.246
What's life? It's one long story.

57:38.329 --> 57:40.123
When the story ends, so does life.

57:40.206 --> 57:42.459
So don't stop me from making jokes.

57:42.542 --> 57:45.211
It's the same thing as killing me.

57:45.295 --> 57:47.714
Even if the world ends tomorrow,

57:47.797 --> 57:49.340
I'll keep cracking jokes

57:49.424 --> 57:51.968
because it's the only proof
of my existence!

57:52.552 --> 57:54.304
What do you keep looking at?

58:00.393 --> 58:01.352
That's right.

58:02.645 --> 58:06.691
Your brother said he'll keep making jokes
and talking behind people's backs,

58:06.774 --> 58:07.984
even if the world ends tomorrow,

58:08.067 --> 58:11.404
because it's too hard
for him to keep quiet!

58:11.988 --> 58:14.991
We need to let people
who can't shut the hell up

58:15.074 --> 58:17.327
run their mouths until they drop dead!

58:17.410 --> 58:19.496
Your brother says
that's how we should live!

58:33.384 --> 58:36.095
Hey, call the cops.

58:36.679 --> 58:37.597
I'll take care of him.

58:38.181 --> 58:39.432
No objections, right?

58:54.614 --> 58:55.657
Oh jeez.

58:55.740 --> 58:57.909
-Hold on.
-Hang on.

58:58.910 --> 58:59.953
Don't do this.

59:03.873 --> 59:04.874
Please calm down!

59:04.958 --> 59:06.167
Get off me!

59:06.918 --> 59:08.461
Wait, don't hit me!

59:10.296 --> 59:11.214
Are you okay?

59:11.297 --> 59:13.466
-Please call the police.
-The police?

59:13.550 --> 59:14.926
Please hurry.

59:35.989 --> 59:41.619
Your address is
37, Hyowon 2-gil, Dongro-gu, Seoul.

59:43.621 --> 59:44.747
Occupation?

59:52.630 --> 59:53.464
Occupation?

01:00:03.975 --> 01:00:05.059
He's a film director.

01:00:07.604 --> 01:00:08.438
Who are you?

01:00:09.397 --> 01:00:10.690
The producer in charge.

01:00:28.124 --> 01:00:29.834
WE ARE ALL TRYING HERE

01:00:48.436 --> 01:00:49.354
The Eight Club?

01:00:49.896 --> 01:00:51.564
Forget it. I'm out.

01:00:51.648 --> 01:00:53.399
That's for you shiny people.

01:00:53.900 --> 01:00:55.276
Doing it alone is exhausting.

01:00:55.860 --> 01:00:57.820
I'll stay by your side and watch you.

01:00:58.571 --> 01:01:01.157
I should be the one swearing, you bastard.

01:01:01.240 --> 01:01:03.868
You stole from someone you shouldn't have.

01:01:03.951 --> 01:01:05.662
You stole from a genius, you bastard.

01:01:05.745 --> 01:01:08.122
She turned out to be closer
than I thought.

01:01:08.623 --> 01:01:10.667
She works at Choi Film.

01:01:11.250 --> 01:01:12.669
-Hi!
-Jang Mi-ran knows me?

01:01:14.045 --> 01:01:16.047
Park Gyeong-se is a bastard
Damn Gyeong-se is a bastard

01:01:16.130 --> 01:01:17.256
Hey, let me ask you something.

01:01:17.340 --> 01:01:19.258
Why have you been so mean to me?

01:01:19.342 --> 01:01:20.968
Because you hated me first.

01:01:22.178 --> 01:01:24.013
What made you hate me so much?

01:01:26.599 --> 01:01:31.604
Subtitle translation by: Jenny Kim
